Indices of personal names, people-names, and place-names follow the text itself. The Introduction includes an account of the manuscript and a linguistic analysis of the E-text. The E-text cannot of course be studied in isolation. This volume is part of the Anglo-Saxon Chronicle Collaborative Series and with its publicationthe Series now includes editions of the main texts through from A to F. A substantial section of the Introduction to the volume is devoted to a detailed discussion of E's complex textual relationships with the other versions of the Chronicle, and also with other relevant documents such as Peterborough Charters and twelfth-century Latin chronicles. Dr SUSAN IRVINE is Senior Lecturer in the Department of English, University College, London.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnglo-SaxonsvEarly works to 1800. 4aBibliography & Manuscripts. 4aMedieval History. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aREFERENCE / Bibliographies & Indexes.2bisacsh  aAnglo-Saxon Chronicle.  aE-text.  aNorthern Recension.  aPeterborough Chronicle.  acomplex textual relationships.  alinguistic analysis.  amanuscripts.1 aIrvine, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrvine, Susan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846152184?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846152184423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846152184/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles